# Trivy filesystem-scan suppressions for carapace.
#
# Use the `<CVE-ID> exp:<YYYY-MM-DD>` form so the next reviewer sees a
# concrete deadline at which the suppression should be re-evaluated.
# Each entry MUST include a comment block above it explaining:
# - what the CVE is,
# - why we cannot remediate today,
# - the upstream fix path,
# - the user-facing exposure / mitigation.

# CVE-2026-6966 — awslabs/tough delegated-roles signature-threshold bypass
# CVE-2026-6967 — awslabs/tough missing delegated-metadata validation
#
# Vulnerable package: tough 0.21.0; fix in tough 0.22.0 (published
# 2026-04-24). Both CVEs are GHSA-8m7c-8m39-rv4x.
#
# Why we cannot remediate today: the only consumer of `tough` in our
# dependency graph is `sigstore-trust-root` 0.6.6 (latest at this
# writing) -> `sigstore-verify` 0.6.6, which pins `tough = "^0.21"`.
# That requirement is semver-incompatible with 0.22.0, so neither a
# direct cargo upgrade nor `[patch.crates-io] tough = "0.22"` will
# satisfy resolution. Forking sigstore-trust-root locally to bump
# tough is high-cost and high-risk for a single-user gateway; the
# pragmatic path is to wait for a sigstore-rs upstream release that
# bumps the pin.
#
# Upstream tracking: sigstore/sigstore-rs (no public issue at this
# writing — re-check before each batch of dep bumps and open one if
# none exists).
#
# User-facing exposure: tough is reachable only via `cara update`'s
# self-update verification path (src/update/mod.rs), which uses
# Sigstore's production TUF infrastructure to load the trust root.
# Both CVEs are exploitable only by an attacker who can serve forged
# TUF metadata to the carapace daemon — i.e. an attacker who has
# compromised Sigstore's TUF servers or the network path between the
# daemon and `tuf-repo-cdn.sigstore.dev`. For carapace specifically,
# `cara update` additionally validates the artifact's Sigstore
# bundle (cosign signature + cert identity) against the expected
# release identity, which is a separate verification layer that
# tough's signature-threshold bypass does NOT defeat. Operators who
# want defense-in-depth can pin to a known release with
# `cara update --version <x.y.z>`, or skip self-update entirely.
#
# Re-evaluate by 2026-08-01 or earlier if sigstore-rs ships a
# tough-0.22-compatible release. Drop both lines and the comment
# block once the lockfile no longer references tough <0.22.
CVE-2026-6966 exp:2026-08-01
CVE-2026-6967 exp:2026-08-01
